        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-458",
        "content": "The forester climbed up, brought the child down, and thought to himself: 'You will take him home with you, and bring him up with your Lina.' He took it home, therefore, and the two children grew up together.",
        "style_prompt": "M_p-low_s-fast_e-low",
        "gender": "M",
