        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-458",
        "content": "Next morning when the cows were being driven out, the little peasant called the cow herd in and said: 'Look, I have a little calf there, but it is still small and has to be carried.' The cow herd said: 'All right,' and took it in his arms and carried it to the pasture, and set it among the grass.",
        "style_prompt": "M_p-low_s-normal_e-normal",
        "gender": "M",
        "pitch": "low",
